doc.after: British colonisation of Australia began with the arrival of the First Fleet in Botany Bay in 1788  One immediate consequence of British settlement was a series of European epidemic diseases such as measles smallpox and tuberculosis In the 19th century smallpox was the principal cause of Aboriginal deaths 46
